Description: Part of a jar-seal: of dull grey clay with a seal-impression of Peribsen. Good condition, with well-preserved inscriptions.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' I, pl.XXIX, 87; W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' II, 12, pl.XXII, 190; H. R. Hall, 'Catalogue of Egyptian scarabs etc. in the British Museum: Volume 1 : Royal scarabs' (London, 1913), 289, no.2765; P. Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit III (Wiesbaden, 1964), pl.95, abb.368; see also vols. I, 158-60 and II, 846, n.952; 1143.
